WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-GB

00:00:40.300 --> 00:00:47.430
In November 2012 Australian ex-Prime Minister
Julia Gillard proposed a Royal Commission

00:00:47.430 --> 00:00:51.540
to investigate institutional responses to
child sexual abuse.

00:00:51.540 --> 00:00:56.030
It covered a range of institutions including
schools, churches and sports clubs

00:00:56.030 --> 00:00:58.460
in a total of 57 public hearings

00:00:58.460 --> 00:01:03.019
recording the testimonies of nearly 7,000
abused individuals

00:01:03.019 --> 00:01:05.150
around 64% of whom were male

00:01:05.150 --> 00:01:10.940
and 10% of whom said it was the first time
they’d told anyone about their abuse.

00:01:10.940 --> 00:01:12.960
There would be testimonies
from people like Hugh

00:01:12.970 --> 00:01:16.100
who was abused around age 10 by a scout leader

00:01:16.100 --> 00:01:20.780
who, after gaining his parents’ trust, had
him over for parties

00:01:20.780 --> 00:01:25.320
where boys were plied with marijuana and alcohol
and molested.

00:01:25.320 --> 00:01:31.700
And like Margaret, who was 11 when she was
abused at a Salvation Army children’s home

00:01:31.700 --> 00:01:34.600
by a church captain who not only molested
children

00:01:34.600 --> 00:01:36.990
but orchestrated their abuse of each other.

00:01:36.990 --> 00:01:42.060
To conduct the Commission’s investigation,
a panel of six commissioners was appointed

00:01:42.060 --> 00:01:44.160
headed by Justice Peter McClellan

00:01:44.160 --> 00:01:48.160
a former Chief Judge for the Supreme Court
of New South Wales

00:01:48.160 --> 00:01:52.780
and Assistant Commissioner for the Independent
Commission Against Corruption.

00:01:52.780 --> 00:01:59.040
In May 2015, the Commission began to investigate
‘case 29’ of their public hearings

00:01:59.040 --> 00:02:04.160
which concerned responses to child sexual
abuse within the Jehovah’s Witness organisation.

00:02:04.160 --> 00:02:09.539
Assisting counsel for the Commission was the
formidable Angus Stewart QC.

00:02:09.539 --> 00:02:11.290
In a video called ‘concealing abuse’

00:02:11.290 --> 00:02:14.380
I looked at how the Jehovah’s Witness organisation
responded

00:02:14.380 --> 00:02:18.860
to real-life allegations of child sexual abuse
against its members

00:02:18.860 --> 00:02:21.880
and how its policies tend to protect the abuser.

00:02:21.880 --> 00:02:26.640
For instance, even if they fully believe the
allegations made against a member

00:02:26.640 --> 00:02:31.140
the congregation’s judicial and spiritual
leaders —&nbsp;known as ‘elders’ —

00:02:31.140 --> 00:02:35.810
won’t take any action unless either there
are at least two witnesses to the abuse

00:02:35.810 --> 00:02:38.900
which is unlikely in view of the private nature
of sexual abuse

00:02:38.900 --> 00:02:44.120
or the abuser confesses voluntarily — which
is again, unlikely.

00:02:44.120 --> 00:02:49.000
Even when these exacting demands are met,
justice is far from guaranteed.

00:02:49.000 --> 00:02:51.760
While the organisation possesses
the judicial apparatus

00:02:51.770 --> 00:02:54.510
to eject molesters from congregations

00:02:54.510 --> 00:02:56.790
it repeatedly fails to use it.

00:02:56.790 --> 00:03:00.140
In a form of excommunication known as disfellowshipping

00:03:00.140 --> 00:03:05.700
individuals judged to be unrepentant sinners
are completely shunned by all members

00:03:05.700 --> 00:03:09.956
including family. But individuals found guilty
of molestation

00:03:09.960 --> 00:03:13.420
can avoid this fate just by apologising.

00:03:13.420 --> 00:03:20.020
If they express repentance to their congregation’s
elders, they can simply be ‘reproved’.

00:03:20.030 --> 00:03:23.780
All this entails is an announcement being
made to their congregation

00:03:23.780 --> 00:03:27.940
that they’ve been reprimanded for an unspecified
transgression.

00:03:27.940 --> 00:03:29.620
And that’s it.

00:03:29.620 --> 00:03:33.760
They’ll be left in the congregation, risking
further molestation

00:03:33.770 --> 00:03:38.020
and the constant retraumatisation of the individuals
they’ve abused

00:03:38.020 --> 00:03:41.850
who often feel forced out of their own congregation.

00:03:41.850 --> 00:03:48.170
These kinds of misguided policies serve to
protect abusers and punish the abused.

00:03:48.170 --> 00:03:51.290
Through its in-depth investigation of individual
cases

00:03:51.290 --> 00:03:57.100
the Australian Royal Commission would expose
a daunting maze of unthinkable additional hurdles

00:03:57.100 --> 00:04:02.700
faced by sexually abused children raised in
the Jehovah’s Witness organisation.

00:04:02.700 --> 00:04:04.410
The Commission focused on the experiences

00:04:04.410 --> 00:04:08.540
of two individuals abused by members of the
organisation.

00:04:08.540 --> 00:04:15.540
For anonymity, the individuals were codenamed
BCB and BCG.

00:04:18.150 --> 00:04:21.400
BCB was the first to take the witness stand.

00:04:21.400 --> 00:04:24.430
She testified to the following account:

00:04:24.430 --> 00:04:26.880
She was born in 1967.

00:04:26.880 --> 00:04:30.520
When she was 10, her mother
became a Jehovah’s Witness

00:04:30.520 --> 00:04:34.060
and started taking her and her brother to
meetings.

00:04:34.070 --> 00:04:38.440
BCB drifted apart from her father who didn’t
attend.

00:04:38.440 --> 00:04:42.130
At age 12, she met Bronwyn and Bill Neill

00:04:42.130 --> 00:04:44.170
and became friends with a daughter of theirs.

00:04:44.170 --> 00:04:47.530
She would attend meetings at their house and
sleep over.

00:04:47.530 --> 00:04:51.509
Mr. Neill discouraged both girls from making
non-Witness friends at school

00:04:51.509 --> 00:04:55.539
based on the idea that ‘bad association
spoils useful habits’

00:04:55.540 --> 00:05:01.760
a sentiment derived from the Biblical passage
1 Corinthians 15:33.

00:05:01.760 --> 00:05:05.319
The sexual jokes Mr. Neill started making
in front of her

00:05:05.319 --> 00:05:09.810
would signal the onset of an escalating pattern
of abuse.

00:05:09.810 --> 00:05:13.050
At age 14, when she stayed over with the Neill
family

00:05:13.050 --> 00:05:17.059
he started inserting his tongue in her mouth
when he kissed her goodnight.

00:05:17.060 --> 00:05:21.140
She would endure these inappropriate kisses
for the next four years.

00:05:21.140 --> 00:05:26.120
She felt ashamed and scared, and worried about
upsetting Mrs. Neill.

00:05:26.120 --> 00:05:31.460
But Mr. Neill was an elder, and she submitted
to his authority.

00:05:31.460 --> 00:05:35.260
When she was 17, he intruded on her while
she was showering

00:05:35.270 --> 00:05:37.800
somehow managing to unlock a locked door.

00:05:37.800 --> 00:05:40.360
He left when she screamed ‘Get out’

00:05:40.360 --> 00:05:46.160
but later gave her a vicious belting for making
too much noise in her bedroom.

00:05:46.160 --> 00:05:51.020
At age 18, she was subjected to more overtly
sexual behaviour.

00:05:51.020 --> 00:05:54.509
He called her a nymphomaniac and a prostitute.

00:05:54.509 --> 00:05:58.789
One time, Mrs. Neill caught him tongue-kissing
BCB and stopped him.

00:05:58.789 --> 00:06:03.240
But nothing further was said or done — and
his forcefulness escalated

00:06:03.240 --> 00:06:07.259
culminating in an incident in which he trapped
BCB in the bathroom

00:06:07.259 --> 00:06:10.880
and violated her manually and orally.

00:06:10.880 --> 00:06:16.379
The next day, he entered her room and suggested
she’d enjoy full intercourse.

00:06:16.379 --> 00:06:22.069
She asked him to leave, then packed and returned
to her parents’ farm.

00:06:22.069 --> 00:06:24.250
The next year, when he heard through his daughter

00:06:24.250 --> 00:06:27.110
that BCB had been seeing a couple of boys

00:06:27.110 --> 00:06:32.120
Neill invoked his role as an elder to summon
her to talk about boys.

00:06:32.120 --> 00:06:34.360
She felt she had no choice.

00:06:34.360 --> 00:06:40.180
He took the opportunity to inspect her physically
and abuse her verbally.

00:06:40.180 --> 00:06:43.880
Two years later in 1989, having married

00:06:43.880 --> 00:06:48.979
she confided in her husband and also a friend
about Neill’s abuse.

00:06:48.979 --> 00:06:52.089
The friend then disclosed this information
to someone else.

00:06:52.089 --> 00:06:58.060
A week or so later, a young elder called Max
Horley approached her to arrange a visit.

00:06:58.060 --> 00:07:01.720
During the visit, he revealed he’d come
to talk about Neill.

00:07:01.720 --> 00:07:06.640
BCB gave some details but was too ashamed
to recount the bathroom incident.

00:07:06.640 --> 00:07:11.760
Horley invited Neill to BCB’s house, to
speak with her and her husband.

00:07:11.760 --> 00:07:15.719
Despite her discomfort at opening up her own
home to her abuser

00:07:15.720 --> 00:07:20.520
she did as she was told on the assumption
that Horley knew the correct procedure.

00:07:20.520 --> 00:07:23.420
She didn’t recall having the purpose of
the meeting explained to her.

00:07:23.439 --> 00:07:27.749
And she felt too inhibited to recount the
full details in front of Neill

00:07:27.749 --> 00:07:32.319
or challenge him when he suggested his behaviour
was meant as a joke.

00:07:32.319 --> 00:07:36.680
Afterwards, BCB approached Horley and gave
more details.

00:07:36.680 --> 00:07:40.849
This led to a second meeting, with the addition
attendance of one Doug Jackson

00:07:40.849 --> 00:07:45.939
a circuit overseer — someone who supervises
multiple congregations.

00:07:45.939 --> 00:07:49.559
His presence and the purpose of the meeting
weren’t explained

00:07:49.560 --> 00:07:52.580
it was just presented as a ‘committee meeting’.

00:07:52.580 --> 00:07:56.399
Neill attempted to blame BCB for wearing revealing
clothes

00:07:56.400 --> 00:08:00.060
but Jackson said the church didn’t accept
that excuse.

00:08:00.060 --> 00:08:06.120
Again Neill’s presence inhibited her, as
did being in a room full of men.

00:08:06.120 --> 00:08:09.840
She said if a female she trusted from the
congregation had been there too

00:08:09.840 --> 00:08:11.760
it might’ve been easier.

00:08:11.760 --> 00:08:16.960
At the end of the meeting, Neill was told
to apologise, which he did.

00:08:16.960 --> 00:08:23.159
BCB was given no explanation of the meeting’s
outcome or of what would happen.

00:08:23.159 --> 00:08:26.529
Jackson gave her an article about child sexual
abuse

00:08:26.529 --> 00:08:30.780
published in one of the organisation’s magazines,
called the Watchtower.

00:08:30.780 --> 00:08:36.640
Not long after this, Mrs. Neill phoned BCB
and told her ‘Bill didn’t abuse you.’

00:08:36.640 --> 00:08:40.680
BCB reported this to Horley, who said he’d
sort it out.

00:08:40.680 --> 00:08:43.100
Later that day, he phoned and said:

00:08:43.100 --> 00:08:46.540
‘The Neills have asked that you not tell
any more people about Bill

00:08:46.540 --> 00:08:49.170
out of respect for the family.’

00:08:49.170 --> 00:08:54.600
Scared, disorientated and unsupported, she
did as she was told.

00:08:54.600 --> 00:08:57.940
It was only years later that she saw the perversity

00:08:57.940 --> 00:09:00.880
of being asked to respect the man who abused
her

00:09:00.880 --> 00:09:05.500
when nobody had offered her the respect or
support she deserved.

00:09:05.500 --> 00:09:11.120
Weeks later, it was announced that Neill had
stepped down as an elder, with no reason given.

00:09:11.120 --> 00:09:14.000
Nobody talked to BCB about her abuse

00:09:14.009 --> 00:09:18.339
and she was still expected to attend study
meetings at the Neills’ house.

00:09:18.339 --> 00:09:23.090
She asked not to go there — but was told
she had to.

00:09:23.090 --> 00:09:25.710
Mrs. Neill ignored her.

00:09:25.710 --> 00:09:31.500
Finally in 1994 she moved from the area to
another congregation.

00:09:31.500 --> 00:09:35.760
In 2012, she gave a written statement to two
elders

00:09:35.769 --> 00:09:39.519
including one Joe Bello, summarising her experience

00:09:39.520 --> 00:09:43.660
in an effort to support the case of anyone
else Neill might’ve abused.

00:09:43.660 --> 00:09:47.670
Eighteen months later, Bello visited on an
unrelated matter

00:09:47.670 --> 00:09:52.770
and BCB told him she was considering reporting
her abuse to the Royal Commission.

00:09:52.770 --> 00:09:55.400
She said Bello later spoke to her husband
and said:

00:09:55.400 --> 00:10:00.360
‘You should ask [BCB] if she really wants
to drag Jehovah’s name through the mud.’

00:10:00.360 --> 00:10:04.520
BCB was dismayed to find that the burden of
Neill’s shameful actions

00:10:04.520 --> 00:10:07.500
had been put on her shoulders.

00:10:07.500 --> 00:10:11.060
Although she eventually reported her experiences
to the Royal Commission

00:10:11.060 --> 00:10:15.949
she suffered extreme misplaced guilt about
betraying the organisation

00:10:15.949 --> 00:10:18.819
guilt that manifested in physical symptoms

00:10:18.819 --> 00:10:23.750
such as chest tightness, heart palpitations
and difficulty breathing.

00:10:23.750 --> 00:10:28.160
She reported that her abuse destroyed her
confidence and self-esteem

00:10:28.160 --> 00:10:33.810
and instilled in her a sense of victimhood and a constant paranoia that people were judging her.

00:10:33.810 --> 00:10:39.750
She went on to experience suicidal thoughts
and a nervous breakdown.

00:10:39.750 --> 00:10:43.339
She said Neill’s position as an elder gave
him power over her

00:10:43.339 --> 00:10:47.769
and suggested that if she’d been allowed
to speak to other children outside the congregation

00:10:47.769 --> 00:10:51.880
they might’ve reported her abuse to the
appropriate authorities.

00:10:51.880 --> 00:10:53.870
She suggested a number of changes

00:10:53.870 --> 00:10:57.540
in the way the organisation dealt with child
sexual abuse.

00:10:57.540 --> 00:11:02.079
She said it should take allegations more seriously
and report them to the police

00:11:02.079 --> 00:11:05.250
give proper support and protection for children

00:11:05.250 --> 00:11:07.790
and not require female targets of male abuse

00:11:07.790 --> 00:11:13.319
to speak in front of a room full of men, including
their alleged abuser.

00:11:13.319 --> 00:11:17.110
She also noted that no compensation was offered.

00:11:17.110 --> 00:11:21.220
The Commission sought to address all of these
issues.

00:11:23.220 --> 00:11:28.700
Max Horley was the next to testify, and sworn
in on a Biblical oath.

00:11:28.700 --> 00:11:30.680
Not long into Horley’s testimony

00:11:30.690 --> 00:11:34.769
assisting counsel Stewart noted that he seemed
hesitant in his recollections

00:11:34.769 --> 00:11:40.100
and asked if this was because of the passage
of time — which Horley affirmed.

00:11:40.100 --> 00:11:43.360
Judge McClellan asked Horley if he’d taken
notes.

00:11:43.370 --> 00:11:47.610
He said he might’ve at the time — but
they would’ve been destroyed.

00:11:47.610 --> 00:11:50.920
When asked why, he said the elders didn’t
want their wives

00:11:50.920 --> 00:11:53.380
knowing what sort of things
they were dealing with

00:11:53.389 --> 00:11:58.040
and that it was also to protect the person
involved and the rest of the congregation

00:11:58.040 --> 00:12:00.780
so they didn’t have to know
about these things.

00:12:00.780 --> 00:12:05.240
It was not only a deeply patronising rationale
but a dangerous one

00:12:05.240 --> 00:12:09.180
leaving congregations unsuspecting about the
molesters in their midst

00:12:09.180 --> 00:12:12.240
which is exactly what molesters want.

00:12:12.240 --> 00:12:17.240
Horley confirmed that destroying notes remained
the current practice.

00:12:17.240 --> 00:12:19.560
When asked if he was aware of his obligations

00:12:19.569 --> 00:12:23.319
to tell authorities about serious allegations
of sexual assault

00:12:23.319 --> 00:12:25.170
Horley showed no awareness

00:12:25.170 --> 00:12:29.400
and said he’d contact his branch for advice
on how to proceed.

00:12:29.400 --> 00:12:33.720
Unthinking deference to the branch would become
a familiar stock response

00:12:33.720 --> 00:12:37.480
from the elders called to testify to the Commission.

00:12:37.480 --> 00:12:41.639
Horley expressed confusion about what constituted
criminal assault

00:12:41.640 --> 00:12:46.500
and later admitted giving no consideration
to reporting it to the police.

00:12:46.500 --> 00:12:50.079
This was an individual invested with the safety
and protection

00:12:50.079 --> 00:12:53.170
of an unquestioningly trusting congregation.

00:12:53.170 --> 00:12:56.420
A shepherd charged with guarding the flock.

00:12:56.420 --> 00:13:00.250
But in the shepherd metaphor, Horley was more
like the sheepdog

00:13:00.250 --> 00:13:03.560
cluelessly obeying the whistles of an unseen
shepherd

00:13:03.560 --> 00:13:08.220
who could just as easily direct him to harm
the sheep as to protect them.

00:13:08.220 --> 00:13:14.220
The Biblical passage Matthew 18:15 has been
cited by the organisation as a basis

00:13:14.230 --> 00:13:19.310
for requiring abused individuals to confront
their abusers with their allegations.

00:13:19.310 --> 00:13:25.020
McClellan asked Horley if he realised how
inappropriate this process of confrontation was.

00:13:25.020 --> 00:13:29.240
Horley said he could understand it now, but
hadn’t reflected on it at the time

00:13:29.240 --> 00:13:32.040
because he was just following procedure.

00:13:32.040 --> 00:13:35.839
He agreed it could be very difficult for people
who’d suffered abuse

00:13:35.840 --> 00:13:39.380
to share everything done to them in front
of their abuser.

00:13:39.380 --> 00:13:43.840
He said the organisation wanted to keep Neill’s
abuse as quiet as possible

00:13:43.840 --> 00:13:48.260
not to try to cover it up, but just to stop
the conversation.

00:13:48.260 --> 00:13:51.360
But almost immediately, he contradicted himself

00:13:51.360 --> 00:13:55.069
saying they would’ve tried to keep the matter
under wraps

00:13:55.069 --> 00:13:57.700
in another words cover it up.

00:13:57.700 --> 00:14:01.000
Stewart made the case to Horley
that by directing BCB

00:14:01.010 --> 00:14:03.839
not to speak to anyone in the congregation

00:14:03.839 --> 00:14:06.660
he left her with no one to talk to.

00:14:06.660 --> 00:14:10.500
Horley suggested that because BCB was still
working in the community

00:14:10.500 --> 00:14:13.889
she could’ve spoken to people outside the
organisation.

00:14:13.889 --> 00:14:16.740
But Stewart pointed out that members are advised
not to have

00:14:16.740 --> 00:14:20.629
close friendships or associations with non-members.

00:14:20.629 --> 00:14:22.819
Horley affirmed that was true

00:14:22.820 --> 00:14:27.640
but said that whether members took that advice
or not was entirely up to them.

00:14:27.640 --> 00:14:30.420
Many of us who’ve experienced abusive environments

00:14:30.430 --> 00:14:33.939
with be familiar with this responsibility-dodging
manoeuvre

00:14:33.939 --> 00:14:39.230
in which individuals are given clear instructions
on what to do or what not to do

00:14:39.230 --> 00:14:43.620
then when they suffer as a direct consequence
of following those instructions

00:14:43.620 --> 00:14:46.560
they’re told they didn’t have to follow
them after all.

00:14:46.560 --> 00:14:49.420
And they’re blamed for their own suffering.

00:14:49.430 --> 00:14:53.529
The fact is Jehovah’s Witnesses are warned
in the strongest terms

00:14:53.529 --> 00:14:57.209
against what are called ‘bad associations’
with non-members

00:14:57.209 --> 00:15:00.840
which they’re told will result in disaster.

00:15:00.840 --> 00:15:04.460
For Horley to suggest that BCB was somehow
supposed to view this

00:15:04.470 --> 00:15:07.800
merely as a piece of advice she was free to
take or leave

00:15:07.800 --> 00:15:10.800
was disingenuous in the extreme.

00:15:10.800 --> 00:15:14.240
Stewart put it to Horley that he was saying
two different things.

00:15:14.240 --> 00:15:17.120
On one hand, saying BCB couldn’t
speak to people

00:15:17.120 --> 00:15:19.490
then on the other, that she could.

00:15:19.490 --> 00:15:23.290
Horley claimed he didn’t mean to cut BCB
off from any support

00:15:23.290 --> 00:15:27.920
but admitted he couldn’t recall arranging
anyone to assist her through the period.

00:15:27.920 --> 00:15:29.680
Stewart produced a letter from Horley

00:15:29.680 --> 00:15:34.040
and the circuit overseer Doug Jackson
to their branch office.

00:15:34.040 --> 00:15:37.899
The letter said: It appears that a number
of brothers know about the matter

00:15:37.899 --> 00:15:42.310
and unfortunately there may be worldly people
who also know.

00:15:42.310 --> 00:15:47.450
‘Worldly’ is the derogatory term Jehovah’s
Witnesses use for non-members.

00:15:47.450 --> 00:15:50.889
Stewart asked why it mattered
if worldly people knew?

00:15:50.889 --> 00:15:56.320
Horley said the organisation didn’t want
anything to detract from their ‘clean’ reputation.

00:15:56.320 --> 00:16:01.940
In fact the organisation is heavily invested
in its reputation among outsiders.

00:16:01.940 --> 00:16:06.160
It seems perverse that it should be so concerned
about what worldly people think

00:16:06.160 --> 00:16:09.760
considering it despises us as debauched and
degenerate

00:16:09.760 --> 00:16:12.900
characterises us as the instigators of broken homes

00:16:12.900 --> 00:16:16.580
illegitimate births and sexually transmitted diseases

00:16:16.580 --> 00:16:19.460
and countless other emotional and physical woes

00:16:19.460 --> 00:16:23.680
and compares us to what it calls ‘death-dealing’
polluted air.

00:16:23.680 --> 00:16:26.319
But of course projecting a ‘clean’ image

00:16:26.319 --> 00:16:29.699
is what the organisation relies on to attract
new members.

00:16:29.699 --> 00:16:33.769
And it has no moral qualms whatsoever about
using deception

00:16:33.769 --> 00:16:36.820
to try and maintain that patently false image.

00:16:36.820 --> 00:16:40.460
It even has a formal policy
called ‘theocratic warfare’

00:16:40.460 --> 00:16:44.220
that gives members explicit permission to
deceive worldly people

00:16:44.220 --> 00:16:47.240
on the grounds that they’re not entitled
to the truth.

